As of the [[census]] of 2010, there were 925 people living in the CDP.  The racial makeup of the CDP was 10.1% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 81.4% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.02% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.03% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.5% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 5.8% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 1.6% of the population.

The median income for a household in the CDP was $49,232. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $28,398. 61.8% of the population were living below the [[poverty line]].

